# Get these from: Supabase Dashboard → Settings → API
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-public-key

# ── DotMail (Resend-first production path) ───────────────────────────────────
# DotMail sending is handled server-side by Supabase Edge Function:
#   supabase/functions/send-emails/index.ts
#
# Required server-side secrets (DO NOT place in client env files):
#   supabase secrets set RESEND_API_KEY=re_...
#   supabase secrets set RESEND_FROM_ADDRESS=no-reply@yourdomain.com
#
# Manual process-queue trigger (local/prod):
#   supabase functions invoke send-emails --no-verify-jwt
#
# Scheduler wiring (pg_cron) and operational steps:
#   docs/dotmail-production-runbook.md

# ── JamalAI Edge Function secrets ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Shared by all three AI functions: jamalaibrain, jamalai-assist, jamalai-gateway
# Set these via: supabase secrets set AI_API_KEY=sk-... AI_BASE_URL=... AI_MODEL=...
# They live only on the Supabase server — never in this .env file or client code.
#
# AI_API_KEY      – API key from your chosen provider (OpenAI, Groq, Together AI, etc.)
# AI_BASE_URL     – Base URL of the OpenAI-compatible endpoint
#                   OpenAI:  https://api.openai.com/v1
#                   Groq:    https://api.groq.com/openai/v1
# AI_MODEL        – Model name, e.g. gpt-4o-mini or llama3-8b-8192
#
# Deploy all three functions to your Supabase project:
#   supabase functions deploy jamalaibrain
#   supabase functions deploy jamalai-assist
#   supabase functions deploy jamalai-gateway
#
# jamalai-gateway is the recommended single entry-point:
#   { prompt }                          → brain (general chat)
#   { module, task, data? }             → assist (module-specific help)
